SIMPLE: inept
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inept
<hw>In*ept"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ineptus</ets>; prefix. <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>aptus</ets> apt,
fit: cf. F. <ets>inepte</ets>. Cf. <er>Inapt</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not apt or fit; unfit; unsuitable; improper;
unbecoming.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Aristotelian philosophy is <qex>inept</qex> for new
discoveries.</q> <rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Silly; useless; nonsensical; absurd;
foolish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To view attention as a special act of intelligence, and to
distinguish it from consciousness, is utterly <qex>inept</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ineptitude</ent>⟦br⟧
